Trapping Rain Water

Topic: Arrays, Two Pointers
Difficulty: Hard

Problem Statement

You are given an array height where each element represents the height of a bar.

After raining, water gets trapped between these bars.

Your task is to calculate how much total water can be trapped.

Example 1
Input:
height = [0,1,0,2,1,0,1,3,2,1,2,1]

Output:
6

Explanation:
Bars ke beech me paani store hota hai. Total trapped water = 6 units

Code:

#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    int trap(vector<int>& height) {

        int left = 0, right = height.size() - 1;
        int leftMax = 0, rightMax = 0;
        int water = 0;

        while(left < right) {

            if(height[left] < height[right]) {

                if(height[left] >= leftMax) {
                    leftMax = height[left];
                } else {
                    water += leftMax - height[left];
                }

                left++;
            }
            else {

                if(height[right] >= rightMax) {
                    rightMax = height[right];
                } else {
                    water += rightMax - height[right];
                }

                right--;
            }
        }

        return water;
    }
};
